What you need to know:  Nine cars were allowed to re-join the rally after they had retired on the previous day of the competition. Such drivers faced extra penalties before being allowed to race again.They included McRae Kimathi, Hamza Anwar, Giancarlo Davite, Paras Pandya, Nikhil Sachania and Steve Mwangi.Anwar set fastest stage time in the penultimate section of the competition to prove he has the ability to stay with the top drivers in his Mitsubishi Lancer.